The paper discusses the dynamics of recommender systems and their impact on user behavior, which falls under the scope of social networks and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also touches upon issues related to user privacy and decision-making, which could be classified under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper proposes a model to study the dynamics of the system, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
